Engineering and construction services provider Fluor South Africa has appointed its first female GM, Tolani Azeez. Azeez has 17 yearsâ€™ experience in project management in international engineering, procurement and construction (EPC) lump sum and reimbursable projects. She recently won the distinguished 2018 European Woman in Construction & Engineering award for best project manager. Azeez said in a statement on Monday that she looks forward to confirming the status of the Fluor South African office as a centre of excellence for EPC services in sub-Saharan Africa and that the company has the capability to expand its region, while being ready to deliver within the optimistic market environment of South Africa and its neighbouring regions.